cs.AI, cs.GT, cs.LG, cs.PL, cs.DS 

This paper focuses on implementing game playing agents for the board game Patchwork, using constraint programming and heuristics. This falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it involves designing agents that can make decisions and play the game. The paper also discusses evaluating different placements, which could fall under game theory (cs.GT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of constraints and modeling could also fall under programming languages (cs.PL) and data structures (cs.DS).
